{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Route Turn After PR Comment",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "After a PR comment is posted, deterministically route the conversation: parse the comment with turn-router-skill.js and invoke the tagged sub-agent(s). Makes the orchestrator-led hand-off reliable instead of depending on GitHub events. Matches the GitHub add_issue_comment tool (and the equivalent GitHub Power call).",
  "when": {
    "type": "postToolUse",
    "toolTypes": [".*add_issue_comment.*", ".*create_pull_request_review.*", ".*kiroPowers.*"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "This hook fires after a comment tool OR any GitHub Power call. FIRST determine whether the tool call that just ran actually posted a PR comment or review (a direct `add_issue_comment`/`create_pull_request_review` call, or a `kiroPowers` call whose `toolName` is one of those). If it did NOT post a comment/review, do nothing. Otherwise, determine the next turn DETERMINISTICALLY:\n\n1. Run `node .kiro/skills/pr-monitoring/turn-router-skill.js '<the comment body you just posted>'` (or require the module and call parseTurn).\n2. Read the returned decision:\n   - If `terminal` is true (a valid master closing comment with APPROVED-BY-MASTER-AGENT): do NOT route further — proceed to the merge/close step (the pre-merge backstop hook will verify the conversation shape).\n   - If `nextActors` is non-empty: for EACH agent in `nextActors`, invoke that sub-agent via invokeSubAgent, passing the PR number and the full comment body as context, instructing them to do the work, push, and post a reply comment tagging @master-agent. When a comment tags TWO or more agents, invoke all of them (multi-agent discussion) and collect every reply before the master takes its next turn.\n   - If `valid` is false (e.g. a non-terminal comment that tags no one, or tags an unknown handle): this is a protocol violation — fix it by editing/reposting the comment so it either tags the correct next actor(s) or is a proper master closing comment. Never leave the loop stalled.\n3. After the invoked sub-agent(s) return, control returns to the master-agent to take the next turn (review again, or close). The master ALWAYS posts the final comment.\n\nOnly act on GitHub comment/review tool calls; ignore unrelated tool calls."
  }
}
